# Playwright Conventions

- Put reusable UI actions/assertions in `tests/page-objects/`. Specs stay thin.
- Smoke specs live under `tests/smoke/` and use the `@smoke` describe tag.
- Page objects expose `goto()` plus `expect…()` methods; match patterns already used for Virtual Assistant.
- Prefer role/text locators (`getByRole`, `getByText`). Avoid brittle CSS/XPath unless necessary.
- Authenticated smokes use the existing Playwright projects (`smoke-app` + `storageState`); do not re-login inline unless testing auth.
- New smokes must be included by existing `testMatch` in `playwright.config.ts`, or update that project’s match list.
- Keep selectors resilient to empty states (page can show “No calls yet” and still be valid).
